children.name: line
children.value: So where were you headed anyways?

children.name: line
children.value: The North Pole. That's were my real home is.

children.name: line
children.value: So Australia wasn’t giving what it needed to give? Kangaroos scare you or what?

children.name: line
children.value: I got brought here when I was just a calf. I don't know much about the North Pole but that I have to get back.

children.name: line
children.value: The heat turned my whole family into roast beef.

children.name: line
children.value: Hmm.. If I keep heading this way I should eventually reach the North Pole.

children.name: line
children.value: You. Yeah you. The goofy-looking deer creature.

children.name: line
children.value: Oh.. hi.. I'm actually a reindeer.

children.name: line
children.value: A reindeer?? So basically a deer but with seasonal DLC?? Love that for you.

children.name: line
children.value: Don’t give me that look, I’m literally fighting for my life in here.

children.name: line
children.value: NO?? Do you not see that the water is literally evaporating in the tank??

children.name: line
children.value: Anyway, help me out of this tank. Just throw me out or seomthing.

eventsFunctionsExtensions.fullName: Auto typing animation for text ("typewriter" effect)
eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: AutoTyping
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: Reveal a text one letter after the other.
description: Reveal a text one letter after the other (a "typewriter" effect).
It can be used for dialogue scenes or visual novels on Text and Bitmap Text objects.
The top-down RPG example uses this extension ([open the project online](https://editor.gdevelop.io/?project=example://top-down-rpg)).

eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: PanelSpriteSlider
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: A draggable slider that users can move to select a numerical value.
description: A draggable slider that users can move to select a numerical value. The slider can be customized with sprites.
There are ready-to-use sliders in the asset-store [settings UI pack](https://editor.gdevelop.io/?initial-dialog=asset-store&asset-pack=settings-ui-settings-ui).

changelog.breaking: - Sliders now use "variants", allowing easy swapping of their visual aspect. You will have to make some adjustments to existing sliders in your project. Follow this [migration documentation](https://wiki.gdevelop.io/gdevelop5/objects/custom-objects-prefab-template/migrate-to-variants/) to do these changes.

eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: SpeedRestrictions
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: Limit the maximum movement and rotation speed of an object from forces or the 2D Physics behavior.
description: Limit the maximum movement and rotation speed of an object from forces or the 2D Physics behavior.
- Add the behavior that matches the method used to move the object (forces or physics)
- Set the maximum speed value in the behavior properties
- This only affects movement caused by forces or physics behavior
- This may not affect movement caused by other behaviors (platformer, top-down, draggable, etc)
